22:51.638 --> 22:54.106
I WANTED TO HAVE SEX
WITH HIM...

22:54.106 --> 22:56.643
UNTIL HE STARTED
TO HURT ME.

22:56.643 --> 22:58.878
- AND YOU ASKED HIM
TO STOP.

22:58.878 --> 23:01.514
- SO WHAT IF I DID?

23:01.514 --> 23:04.016
I'VE MOVED ON.

23:04.016 --> 23:06.786
- KATIE, BY KEEPING QUIET,

23:06.786 --> 23:09.155
YOU'RE GIVING HIM
POWER OVER YOU.

23:09.155 --> 23:11.558
- BETTER THAN THAT MONOLOGUE
HE DID ABOUT JOCELYN PALEY.

23:11.558 --> 23:13.660
I DON'T NEED THAT.

23:16.896 --> 23:19.466
HE'S NOT REALLY A BAD GUY.

23:19.466 --> 23:22.635
IT'S JUST WHEN HE GETS
THAT BELT IN HIS HANDS,

23:22.635 --> 23:24.871
HE LOSES IT.

23:37.617 --> 23:39.886
- SHE WAS IN MY 15TH CENTURY
ITALIAN LITERATURE CLASS.

23:39.886 --> 23:42.589
I WAS HER ADVISOR.
- SO...

23:42.589 --> 23:45.091
YOU WERE CLOSE.

23:45.091 --> 23:48.094
HAVE YOU READ HER BOOK?

23:48.094 --> 23:50.997
- I OVERHEARD FACULTY
TALK ABOUT IT.

23:50.997 --> 23:53.500
- WELL, JOCELYN
SEEMS PRETTY, UH,

23:53.500 --> 23:55.668
UNSOPHISTICATED
FOR THAT WORLD.

23:55.668 --> 24:00.106
ANY IDEA HOW SHE GOT INVOLVED
WITH DOMINATION, SUBMISSION?

24:00.106 --> 24:02.108
- I HONESTLY COULDN'T SAY.

24:02.108 --> 24:05.745
- WELL, HER HEROINE
GETS DOMINATED BY AN OLDER MAN.

24:05.745 --> 24:08.815
ANY PROFESSORS HERE WHO MIGHT
HAVE INSPIRED THAT STORY?

24:08.815 --> 24:12.519
- TEN YEARS AGO, YES.
BUT...THESE DAYS?

24:12.519 --> 24:13.920
- I HEAR YOU.

24:13.920 --> 24:16.155
WELL, HEY,
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

24:16.155 --> 24:18.491
- PLEASURE.
- MM.

24:18.491 --> 24:20.727
THAT'S A PRETTY FANCY PIANO.

24:20.727 --> 24:23.062
- IT'S A HARPSICHORD.

24:23.062 --> 24:25.498
THEY SAY IT BELONGED
TO ALBINONI.

24:25.498 --> 24:27.166
- ALBINONI?
- MM-HMM.

24:27.166 --> 24:29.536
- YEAH, MY WIFE,
SHE LOVES HIS, UH...

24:29.536 --> 24:31.538
WHAT WAS THAT FAMOUS PIECE
OF HIS?

24:31.538 --> 24:33.172
- HIS ADAGIO?
- ADAGIO.

24:33.172 --> 24:35.508
- IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

24:35.508 --> 24:37.176
IT'S HIS MOST WELL-KNOWN WORK.

24:37.176 --> 24:39.812
AND FUNNY THING IS,
IT ISN'T HIS.

24:39.812 --> 24:43.149
HIS BIOGRAPHER COMPOSED IT
TWO CENTURIES LATER.

24:43.149 --> 24:45.718
- NO KIDDING.

24:45.718 --> 24:47.219
- WE SPOKE TO
JOCELYN'S BOYFRIEND, TEACHERS,

24:47.219 --> 24:48.855
AND ROOMMATES.

24:48.855 --> 24:51.658
THE DARKEST SHE EVER GOT
BEFORE THIS NOVEL WAS SASSY.

24:51.658 --> 24:53.526
- SO SHE'S BEEN
TELLING US THE TRUTH.

24:53.526 --> 24:55.528
- ANY OTHER CAIN VICTIMS?
- THERE'S THREE INTERNS.

24:55.528 --> 24:58.598
HE BROKE ONE OF THEIR WRISTS,
BUT EVEN SHE WON'T TESTIFY.

24:58.598 --> 25:00.066
- SHE INSISTS
THAT CAIN'S A GOOD GUY

25:00.066 --> 25:01.701
EXCEPT WHEN HE HAS
A BELT IN HIS HAND.

25:01.701 --> 25:03.670
- NO WITNESSES.
HE SAID, SHE SAID.

25:03.670 --> 25:05.071
AT LEAST THAT MEANS
HE'LL TAKE THE STAND.

25:05.071 --> 25:07.306
- IT'S AMARO.
- HE DIDN'T COME BACK WITH YOU?

25:07.306 --> 25:09.542
- HE'S LIKE A DOG
WITH A BONE DOWN THERE.

25:09.542 --> 25:11.243
- HEY, NICK, YOU'RE ON
SPEAKER PHONE WITH THE D.A.--

25:11.243 --> 25:13.746
- FOUR DAYS, YOU CAN'T FIND
THE GUY WHO GOT HER INTO THIS?

25:13.746 --> 25:15.548
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?
- MAYBE WE'RE ASKING

25:15.548 --> 25:16.749
THE WRONG QUESTION.
LOOK, I NEED ANOTHER DAY.

25:16.749 --> 25:18.250
- DON'T HAVE IT.

25:18.250 --> 25:20.252
I'M TAKING JOCELYN
TO THE GRAND JURY NOW.

25:24.323 --> 25:26.793
- I WAS INVITED
ONTO ADAM CAIN'S TALK SHOW

25:26.793 --> 25:28.595
TO DISCUSS THE BOOK
I HAD WRITTEN.

25:28.595 --> 25:30.062
- TWENTY-FIVE ACTS.
- YES.

25:30.062 --> 25:31.330
- WHAT HAPPENED
AFTER THE SHOW?

25:31.330 --> 25:33.065
- ADAM CAIN TOOK ME OUT
FOR DRINKS,

25:33.065 --> 25:34.734
THEN TO HIS APARTMENT.

25:34.734 --> 25:36.235
WE WERE GETTING INTIMATE,

25:36.235 --> 25:40.573
THEN SUDDENLY
HE JUST TURNED VIOLENT.

25:40.573 --> 25:42.875
- ALL I CAN SAY,
TODAY'S GRAND JURY INDICTMENT

25:42.875 --> 25:44.644
IS THE FIRST STEP
TOWARDS ACHIEVING JUSTICE

25:44.644 --> 25:46.746
FOR JOCELYN PALEY.
- THE D.A.'S OFFICE

25:46.746 --> 25:48.214
IS DESPERATELY
TRYING TO DISTRACT

25:48.214 --> 25:50.617
FROM THEIR RECENT SCANDAL
WITH A HIGH-PROFILE CASE.

25:50.617 --> 25:52.619
- DON'T GIVE ME THAT--WHETHER
YOU'RE A JOHN IN THE SOUTH BRONX

25:52.619 --> 25:54.320
OR A $3-MILLION-A-YEAR
TALK SHOW HOST,

25:54.320 --> 25:56.656
NO MEANS NO.

25:56.656 --> 25:58.124
- WHEN THE JURY COMPARES
HER ACCUSATIONS

25:58.124 --> 26:00.259
WITH THE CHAPTERS
FROM HER BOOK,

26:00.259 --> 26:02.895
THIS CASE FALLS APART
LIKE A HOUSE OF CARDS.

26:02.895 --> 26:05.564
THAT'S ALL I GOT TODAY,
BOYS AND GIRLS.

26:07.033 --> 26:09.368
- DETECTIVE,
I'M JUST ON MY WAY HOME.

26:09.368 --> 26:11.938
- WELL, I'LL WALK YOU
TO YOUR CAR.

26:11.938 --> 26:13.873
YOU KNOW, I SPENT THE NIGHT
READING YOUR WORK.

26:13.873 --> 26:16.208
YOU'RE QUITE PROLIFIC.

26:16.208 --> 26:19.078
- ACADEMIA:
PUBLISH OR PERISH.

26:19.078 --> 26:23.115
- I LIKE THE ARTICLE YOU WROTE
ON THE ECSTASY OF ST. TERESA.

26:23.115 --> 26:26.052
"THE PAIN WAS SO GREAT
THAT IT MADE ME MOAN..."

26:26.052 --> 26:30.056
- "OVER AND OVER AND THROUGH ME
INTO SWEET DELIGHT."

26:30.056 --> 26:31.958
IT'S FROM HER AUTOBIOGRAPHY.

26:31.958 --> 26:33.693
- OH, YOU TAUGHT IT
IN CLASS.

26:33.693 --> 26:36.729
WELL, THIS IS FROM
JOCELYN'S BOOK, UH...

26:36.729 --> 26:39.699
"THE PAIN WAS SO GREAT,
SUCH SWEET DELIGHT,

26:39.699 --> 26:42.168
I MOANED OVER AND OVER."

26:42.168 --> 26:44.336
- DIDN'T REALIZE SHE WAS PAYING
SUCH CLOSE ATTENTION.

26:44.336 --> 26:47.339
- HUH.

26:47.339 --> 26:50.409
YOU KNOW, SHE'S MAKING
MILLIONS A WEEK.

26:50.409 --> 26:52.411
YOU HAVE A CASE HERE
FOR PLAGIARISM.

26:52.411 --> 26:55.114
- PLEASE, NO.
LAST THING I NEED

26:55.114 --> 26:57.650
IS TO BE ASSOCIATED
WITH A BOOK LIKE THAT.

26:57.650 --> 26:59.952
- OH, WELL, NOW I GET IT.

26:59.952 --> 27:01.688
YOUR ANTIQUE HARPSICHORD--

27:01.688 --> 27:03.890
SOMEONE BOUGHT IT LAST MONTH
AT SOTHEBY'S

27:03.890 --> 27:08.260
FOR $285,000.

27:15.401 --> 27:17.336
- MORE QUESTIONS?
WHY?

27:17.336 --> 27:19.371
- WE'RE WORRIED THE DEFENSE
IS GOING TO PRODUCE THE MAN

27:19.371 --> 27:21.040
THAT YOU BASED THE BOOK ON.

27:21.040 --> 27:23.142
- I TOLD YOU, IT'S FICTION.

27:23.142 --> 27:24.376
- BUT, JOCELYN,
IT'S SO SPECIFIC,

27:24.376 --> 27:26.713
YOU MUST HAVE EXPERIMENTED
WITH SUBMISSION.

27:26.713 --> 27:29.415
- WELL, IN COLLEGE.
- NOT WITH CRAIG.

27:30.783 --> 27:32.284
COME ON, THE ONLY KNOTS
HE'S EVER TIED

27:32.284 --> 27:34.286
WAS WHEN HE WAS
IN THE BOY SCOUTS.

27:34.286 --> 27:36.923
- YEAH, NOT CRAIG.
ANOTHER GUY.

27:36.923 --> 27:38.324
- OH, SO YOU CHEATED ON HIM.

27:38.324 --> 27:40.026
- WHAT?
NO.

27:40.026 --> 27:42.194
- NO?

27:42.194 --> 27:44.363
- I DID A SEMESTER ABROAD.

27:44.363 --> 27:47.934
THE CHARACTER'S
BASED ON...

27:47.934 --> 27:49.435
SOMEONE I MET IN THE VILLA.

27:49.435 --> 27:51.704
HE WAS INTO BONDAGE.
WHY DOES ANY OF THIS MATTER?

27:51.704 --> 27:53.372
- WHERE'D YOU MEET HIM?
A HOTEL?

27:53.372 --> 27:56.475
HIS HOME?
DO YOU HAVE HIS ADDRESS?

27:56.475 --> 27:59.478
- I DON'T.
WHAT IS THIS, 20 QUESTIONS?

27:59.478 --> 28:03.349
- NO, JOCELYN, JUST ONE.

28:03.349 --> 28:06.052
WHO WROTE THE BOOK?

28:17.029 --> 28:20.366
- YOU FOUND OUT?

28:20.366 --> 28:21.433
HOW?

28:21.433 --> 28:22.301
- I TOLD YOU THE FIRST DAY

28:22.301 --> 28:24.470
THE ONE THING YOU DECIDE
NOT TO TELL US

28:24.470 --> 28:27.006
IS THE ONE THING THE DEFENSE
IS GONNA USE TO DESTROY YOU.

28:27.006 --> 28:28.875
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

28:28.875 --> 28:33.145
- BARBA, SHE GETS IT.

28:33.145 --> 28:34.814
- DO THEY KNOW?

28:34.814 --> 28:38.484
- NO, BUT WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TELL THEM.

28:38.484 --> 28:43.022
- NO, N--YOU CAN'T.

28:43.022 --> 28:46.525
YOU CAN'T TELL ANYONE.
IT'LL...RUIN MY CAREER.

28:46.525 --> 28:48.194
MY LIFE.

28:48.194 --> 28:51.497
PLEASE DON'T--
DON'T TELL ANYONE.

29:00.039 --> 29:01.173
- IT WAS PROFESSOR DOBSON'S
IDEA

29:01.173 --> 29:02.474
TO PUT MY NAME ON THE BOOK.

29:02.474 --> 29:04.176
SHE IS AN ACADEMIC.

29:04.176 --> 29:06.012
SHE WAS WORRIED
ABOUT HER REPUTATION.

29:06.012 --> 29:07.880
- AND YOU WEREN'T WORRIED
ABOUT YOURS?

29:07.880 --> 29:09.816
- I OWE $90,000
IN COLLEGE DEBT.

29:09.816 --> 29:12.852
THE YEAR BEFORE THIS
I MADE $2,600 WRITING.

29:12.852 --> 29:15.788
SHE GAVE ME 10%.
I'VE MADE CONNECTIONS.

29:15.788 --> 29:17.456
- YOU WERE RAPED.

29:17.456 --> 29:20.292
- AND YOU LIED
TO THE GRAND JURY.

29:20.292 --> 29:22.829
- I HAD TO. IF I EVER SAY
I DIDN'T WRITE THE BOOK,

29:22.829 --> 29:24.130
I LOSE ALL THE MONEY.

29:24.130 --> 29:25.898
- THAT'S PART
OF THE BOOK CONTRACT?

29:25.898 --> 29:28.234
- YES.

29:28.234 --> 29:30.302
I-I WANNA DROP THE CHARGES.

29:30.302 --> 29:32.004
I CAN'T TESTIFY.
- DROP THE CHARGES,

29:32.004 --> 29:33.906
AND YOUR SECRET'S
GONNA COME OUT ANYWAY

29:33.906 --> 29:35.474
WHEN I INDICT YOU.

29:35.474 --> 29:38.477
LYING TO THE GRAND JURY?
THAT'S A CRIME.

29:38.477 --> 29:40.279
- YOU'LL INDICT ME?

29:40.279 --> 29:43.482
- YOU DON'T TESTIFY,
YOU'RE LOOKING AT PERJURY.

29:43.482 --> 29:45.985
- [stammering]
I CAN'T.

29:48.320 --> 29:51.157
- THAT WAS HARDBALL.
- I WASN'T PLAYING.

29:51.157 --> 29:54.193
- YEAH, I GOT THAT.

29:54.193 --> 29:56.963
DOES THIS IN ANY WAY
POSSIBLY HELP US?

29:56.963 --> 29:58.965
YOU WERE WORRIED
THAT THE JURY

29:58.965 --> 30:00.199
WAS GONNA HOLD THE BOOK
AGAINST HER,

30:00.199 --> 30:02.568
BUT SHE DIDN'T WRITE IT,
SO...

30:02.568 --> 30:04.503
- THEY'LL SEE HER
AS A LIAR.

30:09.541 --> 30:11.577
- MISS PALEY,
COULD YOU TELL THE JURY

30:11.577 --> 30:14.380
WHY YOU AGREED
TO SAY YOU WROTE THIS BOOK?

30:14.380 --> 30:17.049
- I HAD COLLEGE DEBT.
MY PARENTS ARE WORKING CLASS.

30:17.049 --> 30:18.885
WE NEEDED THE MONEY.

30:18.885 --> 30:20.452
- SO YOU DIDN'T
WRITE ONE WORD OF THE BOOK?

30:20.452 --> 30:23.289
YOU'RE NOT INTO BEING...
DOMINATED?

30:23.289 --> 30:26.192
- I WAS PLAYING A ROLE.
IT'S NOT ME.

30:26.192 --> 30:28.494
- BUT IT WAS YOU WHO FLIRTED
WITH THE DEFENDANT

30:28.494 --> 30:31.130
AND WENT HOME WITH HIM
THAT NIGHT.

30:31.130 --> 30:33.199
- IT ALL SEEMED
GLAMOROUS AT FIRST.

30:33.199 --> 30:35.067
HE WAS CHARMING.

30:35.067 --> 30:38.470
I WANTED TO HAVE SEX,
UNTIL HE STARTED HURTING ME.

30:38.470 --> 30:41.073
- AND WHAT DID YOU DO THEN?
- I ASKED HIM TO STOP.

30:41.073 --> 30:44.076
- DID HE?

30:44.076 --> 30:47.413
DID HE?

30:50.149 --> 30:52.919
I KNOW THIS IS DIFFICULT.

30:52.919 --> 30:55.254
- NO, HE DID NOT.

30:55.254 --> 30:58.157
HE FORCED HIMSELF INSIDE ME,

30:58.157 --> 30:59.225
CHOKED ME WITH HIS BELT.

30:59.225 --> 31:01.593
I COULDN'T TALK.

31:01.593 --> 31:04.563
THE MORE I CRIED,
THE MORE HE HU--HURT ME.

31:04.563 --> 31:06.565
- AND THE NEXT NIGHT,
MISS PALEY,

31:06.565 --> 31:08.634
WHAT HAPPENED THEN?

31:08.634 --> 31:11.203
- ADAM CAIN STALKED ME
AT A MAGAZINE PARTY,

31:11.203 --> 31:16.375
TRAPPED ME IN AN ELEVATOR,
AND RAPED ME...AGAIN.

31:16.375 --> 31:18.677
- CAN YOU TELL THE JURY
WHAT CONSEQUENCES YOU FACE

31:18.677 --> 31:21.981
FOR TELLING THE TRUTH
HERE TODAY?

31:21.981 --> 31:24.616
- I HAVE TO RETURN
ALL OF MY ROYALTIES.

31:24.616 --> 31:27.553
MY REPUTATION IS RUINED.

31:27.553 --> 31:29.989
I'VE WANTED TO WRITE
MY WHOLE LIFE.

31:29.989 --> 31:33.059
- THANK YOU, MISS PALEY.

31:33.059 --> 31:34.626
- HOW MANY TIMES HAVE YOU LIED
ABOUT WRITING THE BOOK

31:34.626 --> 31:37.329
TWENTY-FIVE ACTS?

31:37.329 --> 31:39.131
- I'M NOT SURE.

31:39.131 --> 31:42.368
- YOU LIED WHEN YOU CONSENTED
TO HAVE YOUR NAME ON THE COVER.

31:42.368 --> 31:44.036
- YES.
- AND YOU LIED

31:44.036 --> 31:46.638
AT SPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS,
PARTIES, AND INTERVIEWS

31:46.638 --> 31:48.975
IN OVER TEN CITIES
ON YOUR BOOK TOUR.

31:48.975 --> 31:50.709
- YES.
- AND YOU LIED

31:50.709 --> 31:52.578
ON MR. CAIN'S TV SHOW?

31:52.578 --> 31:55.581
BEFORE YOU ANSWER THAT,
MISS PALEY--

31:55.581 --> 31:58.250
DEFENSE EXHIBIT 12,
YOUR HONOR.

31:58.250 --> 32:00.152
- SO, JOCELYN, TELL ME,

32:00.152 --> 32:03.589
WHY DO WOMEN
WANT TO BE DOMINATED?

32:03.589 --> 32:06.158
- WOMEN DO IT ALL THESE DAYS.
CAREER, KIDS.

32:06.158 --> 32:07.593
SOMETIMES THEY JUST WANT A MAN

32:07.593 --> 32:10.129
TO THROW THEM DOWN
AND TAKE CONTROL.

32:10.129 --> 32:13.632
- AND IS THIS
YOUR PERSONAL FANTASY?

32:13.632 --> 32:16.969
- MY FANTASY...
BEING HERE WITH YOU.

32:16.969 --> 32:21.140
[laughter]

32:21.140 --> 32:23.075
- WAS WHAT WE JUST SAW
A LIE TOO?

32:23.075 --> 32:26.378
- I WAS PLAYING A PART,
FLIRTING.

32:26.378 --> 32:28.647
- PLAYING A ROLE FOR PUBLICITY,
MONEY.

32:28.647 --> 32:30.516
- YES.
- WHAT ELSE WOULD YOU DO

32:30.516 --> 32:32.518
FOR MONEY?
LIE ABOUT RAPE?

32:32.518 --> 32:35.487
SUE MY CLIENT?
- NO, I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

32:35.487 --> 32:37.689
- YOU WOULDN'T LIE
ABOUT SEX FOR MONEY?

32:37.689 --> 32:39.225
- NO.
- BUT YOU HAVE LIED

32:39.225 --> 32:41.027
ABOUT SEX FOR MONEY
IN THE PAST.

32:41.027 --> 32:43.129
- I'M TELLING
THE TRUTH NOW.

32:43.129 --> 32:45.697
- I SEE. AND HOW DO YOU EXPECT
THE JURY TO TELL THE DIFFERENCE?

32:45.697 --> 32:48.067
WITHDRAWN.

32:52.304 --> 32:53.739
- I KNEW THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

32:53.739 --> 32:55.374
- YOU TOLD THEM
WHAT HE DID TO YOU.

32:55.374 --> 32:56.642
YOU CONFRONTED HIM.

32:56.642 --> 32:58.744
NO ONE CAN TAKE THAT
AWAY FROM YOU.

32:58.744 --> 33:01.347
- THAT WAS BRUTAL.
- WE'VE GOT ONE HAIL MARY.

33:01.347 --> 33:03.682
PROFESSOR DOBSON, I CAN USE HER
TO REHABILITATE.

33:03.682 --> 33:07.053
- SHE AGREED TO COME?
- SURE, AFTER I SUBPOENAED HER.

33:10.622 --> 33:12.391
PROFESSOR DOBSON,

33:12.391 --> 33:15.727
DID YOU WRITE TWENTY-FIVE ACTS?
- YES.

33:15.727 --> 33:18.364
I'M AFRAID SO.
THE ENTIRE BOOK.

33:18.364 --> 33:20.132
- AND WHO, UH--
WHO DECIDED

33:20.132 --> 33:22.634
TO PUT JOCELYN PALEY
ON THE COVER?

33:22.634 --> 33:24.736
- I DID.
I KNEW THAT TALK SHOW HOSTS

33:24.736 --> 33:27.706
WOULDN'T WANT TO DISCUSS
MY SEXUAL FANTASIES.

33:27.706 --> 33:29.575
- SO THESE FANTASIES
IN THE BOOK,

33:29.575 --> 33:32.511
THESE ARE YOUR FANTASIES,
NOT JOCELYN'S.

33:32.511 --> 33:36.282
- YES, ALL OF THEM.

33:36.282 --> 33:38.450
- BEFORE JOCELYN AGREED
TO HELP YOU,

33:38.450 --> 33:40.819
DID SHE KNOW
THE SUBJECT MATTER?

33:40.819 --> 33:43.222
- HARDLY.
WHEN SHE READ THE DRAFT,

33:43.222 --> 33:45.324
SHE WAS...SHOCKED.

33:45.324 --> 33:47.559
THAT'S WHEN I KNEW
SHE'D BE THE PERFECT FRONT.

33:47.559 --> 33:50.396
- WHY WAS THAT?
- SHE WAS A SWEET GIRL.

33:50.396 --> 33:52.064
AND THE CONTRAST
BETWEEN HER INNOCENCE

33:52.064 --> 33:53.732
AND THE BOOK'S
INTENSE SEXUALITY

33:53.732 --> 33:55.834
WAS COMPELLING.

33:55.834 --> 33:58.670
- HAS IT BEEN HARD FOR YOU
TO OUT YOURSELF?

33:58.670 --> 34:01.340
- IN MY WORLD, I'M BETWEEN
A PARIAH AND A LAUGHINGSTOCK.

34:01.340 --> 34:03.742
THAT'S WHY I WANTED
TO USE JOCELYN'S NAME.

34:03.742 --> 34:06.778
BUT TO THINK THAT SOMEONE WOULD
ASCRIBE MY FANTASIES TO HER

34:06.778 --> 34:09.448
AND USE THAT AS
A SMOKESCREEN FOR ASSAULT...

34:09.448 --> 34:13.319
WELL, IT SICKENS ME.

34:13.319 --> 34:14.586
- ABOUT THOSE FANTASIES
IN YOUR BOOK--

34:14.586 --> 34:16.788
DID ANYONE ELSE KNOW
THAT JOCELYN PALEY

34:16.788 --> 34:18.724
WASN'T THE REAL AUTHOR?

34:18.724 --> 34:20.726
- NO.
- SO THE REST OF THE WORLD,

34:20.726 --> 34:23.462
INCLUDING MR. CAIN,
BELIEVED THE BOOK WAS BASED

34:23.462 --> 34:26.365
ON JOCELYN PALEY'S FANTASIES?

34:26.365 --> 34:27.799
- I SUPPOSE SO.
- THAT SHE WAS THE ONE

34:27.799 --> 34:30.736
WHO FANTASIZED
ABOUT BEING DOMINATED,

34:30.736 --> 34:35.207
HAVING ROUGH SEX,
HAVING SEX IN AN ELEVATOR?

34:35.207 --> 34:37.676
- YES.
- AND YOU CHOSE MISS PALEY

34:37.676 --> 34:40.812
BECAUSE SHE WAS
A SWEET, INNOCENT GIRL?

34:40.812 --> 34:42.214
- YES.

34:42.214 --> 34:44.450
- YOU'RE A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.

34:44.450 --> 34:47.819
YOU MUST SEE A LOT
OF SWEET, INNOCENT GIRLS.

34:47.819 --> 34:49.855
- NOT AS MANY
AS YOU'D THINK.

34:49.855 --> 34:52.391
- WHAT MADE JOCELYN PALEY

34:52.391 --> 34:55.194
THE RIGHT CHOICE?
